####################################
# HANDLE CHANGED FEAT PREREQUISITE #
####################################
# According to RGG version 8, pp 8, "Feats and Traits" if a feat's prerequisites have changed, a PC may switch to the updated feat, ignoring the prerequisites or keep the feat or or retrain it at no cost.
# One such feat issue is that "Improved Two-Weapon Feint" didn't originionally require "Two-Weapon Feint" as a prerequisite.
Improved Two-Weapon Feint (PFS Errata)				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.PFS						PREABILITY:3,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise,Improved Two-Weapon Fighting,Two-Weapon Fighting																																												PREMULT:1,[PRESTAT:1,INT=13],[PREVARGTEQ:CombatFeatIntRequirement,13]																																																																																																	PREMULT:1,[PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,17],[PREVARGTEQ:FeatDexRequirement,17]		PRETOTALAB:6																																DESC:You had Improved Two-Weapon Feint prior to the errata that added the Two-Weapon Feint prerequisite. You are permitted to switch to the updated feat, ignoring the prerequisites.																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.8															ABILITY:FEAT|VIRTUAL|Improved Two-Weapon Feint


